cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is about talking face synthesis using a two-stream network that generates facial animations by merging features from multiple source images. This involves techniques such as landmark detection, facial region warping, and attention-based merging. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also involves some level of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and graphics (cs.GR) in terms of rendering facial organs and creating facial animations.
